  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee and coordinate <strong>Mechanical &amp; Electrical (M&amp;E) works</strong> to ensure alignment with project schedules and requirements.</li>\n  <li>Interpret M&amp;E drawings, specifications, and shop drawings to ensure compliance with design intent and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and inspect M&amp;E installation works, ensuring quality, safety, and proper execution.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with contractors, consultants, architects, and suppliers to resolve technical issues and site constraints.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all M&amp;E works comply with relevant building codes, regulations, and workplace safety requirements.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the testing, commissioning, and handover of M&amp;E systems to ensure proper functionality.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate site records, progress reports, and necessary documentation per project and ISO standards.</li>\n  <li>Identify and resolve site issues related to M&amp;E systems, minimizing disruptions to project progress.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree or Diploma in Mechanical, Electrical, or Building Services Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Minimum<strong> 5 years </strong>of experience in M&amp;E coordination for construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of M&amp;E systems, installation procedures, and industry regulations.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in AutoCAD, Revit, or other M&amp;E design software.</li>\n  <li>Ability to read and interpret M&amp;E drawings and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with local building codes, safety standards, and compliance requirements.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication, coordination, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Experience in testing, commissioning, and handover of M&amp;E systems is an advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
